subSubSection.paragraph:
Prosimulium tomosvaryi

is a geographically widespread morphospecies, ranging across ecoregions from Britain to 
Azerbaijan
, and on that basis it is a good candidate for cryptic species. It has been characterized chromosomally in the centre (
Basrur, 1959
), southwestern (
Morocco
; 
Adler & Belqat, 2001
) and, now, south-eastern (
Armenia
) portions of its distribution.
